Write a function to find the longest common prefix string amongst an array of strings.

If there is no common prefix, return an empty string "".




intuition - if we sort a string it sorts according to ASCII values. So it will sort the whole array in a order in which first and last have the maximum difference. 
            Now we ca njust compare 2 elements of strs instead of whole array......................       btw its runtime complexity beats 100%


class Solution:
    def longestCommonPrefix(self, strs: List[str]) -> str:
        s=sorted(strs)
        z,i='',0
        for i in range(min(len(s[0]),len(s[-1]))):
            if s[0][i]!=s[-1][i]:
                return z
            z+=s[0][i]
        return z




java

intuition - use stringbuffer because strings is immutable but change stringbuffer back to string while returning(because our method accept string as the output).
            Sorting because first and the last strings of the array will be the most different ones. Then just compare both elements , and return the part that matches.





class Solution {
    public String longestCommonPrefix(String[] strs) {
       StringBuffer sb=new StringBuffer();
       if (strs == null || strs.length == 0) {
            return "";
        }
       Arrays.sort(strs);
       int s=Math.min(strs[0].length(),strs[strs.length-1].length());
       for(int i=0;i<s;i++){
            if(strs[0].charAt(i) != strs[strs.length-1].charAt(i)){
                break;
            }
            sb.append(strs[0].charAt(i));
       }
       
       return sb.toString();
    }
}
